post_text:
Ms. Barker is the next fantastic teacher in our Meet the Staff Series:

Hello there! I graduated from the Central State University in 2011 with a Bachelor of Science in Early Childhood Education. After graduation, I began working with preschoolers in daycare for 2 years. I received my license to teach in 2013 and have been teaching for 3 years as a Kindergarten and First grade teacher.I believe in working with parents, other teachers, and administrators to ensure that all students have every opportunity to learn. In May 2015, I graduated from Concordia University with a Master’s degree in Educational Leadership. I believe in being a lifelong learner. In my free time, I love sports, spending time outdoors, painting, and making music! I am so happy to be at Clark Prep!

post_text:
Next up in our Meet the Staff Series is the wonderful Mrs. Schulz:

Hello, I am Christie Schulz and I am the third grade teacher for Clark Prep. I have lived in Urbana all of my life, but have taught in Springfield for most of my career. I earned my Bachelor's degree in Elementary education from Urbana University and my Master's degree from Northern Arizona University. I have fifteen years of experience teaching students in grades three through eight. I enjoy spending time with my family. I am very excited to be joining the wonderful family of staff, students, and parents at Clark Prep!

post_text:
Our Meet the Staff series continues with the lovely Ms. Tobias who will be teaching our 4/5 ELA/Social Studies classes:

Hello! My name is Whitney Tobias and I have been in the Dayton area for my entire life. After graduating from Beavercreek High School, I continued my education at Wright State University where I received both a B.S. and M.Ed in Middle Childhood Education. Upon completion of my schooling in 2013, I worked in both a large public district and a small private school. These positions have provided me with a wide variety of experiences. I am an avid reader, football fanatic, and a lover of all things dogs. I look forward to bringing my insight and knowledge to the Clark team!

post_text:
Our Meet the Staff Series continues with the wonderful Mrs.Johanna Sawyer-Clausen aka Ms. Jo!

Hello, all! I am a Springfield native, though I lived out-of-state while working on my Bachelor's degree. I earned my BSEd in History and English Education from the University of South Dakota in 2009. I stayed home for a few years after school to raise my three daughters, then began working on my Master's degree. I graduated from the University of Nebraska at Kearney in May 2017 with an MSEd degree in Curriculum Development and Instruction. Currently, I am working on finishing a Reading endorsement through the same university. I am very excited to continue teaching middle school Social Studies and English/Language Arts at Clark Prep! #clarkpreprocks

post_text:
New Online Videos Help Parents Support the Third Grade Reading Guarantee
3/14/2016

Reading on the Go, Reading for a Purpose and Reading on the Screen, short vidoes that are less than three minutes, give parents concrete, easy tips to help their children become stronger readers and meet the Third Grade Reading Guarantee. The videos, developed to assist parents as they help their children practice reading, are perfect for sharing during parent nights and come with a collection of companion flyers with even more tips for parents. Find them all on INFOhio’s Third Grade Reading Guarantee page.

The flyers and videos were developed by INFOhio, the State Library of Ohio, the Ohio Educational Library Media Association, and the Ohio PTA. They are available to all Ohioans for free download. For more information and easy ways to communicate with your parents about the videos, go to the Online Video announcement on the INFOhio website.

https://vimeo.com/149091464

https://vimeo.com/149151138
